servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Trim root end from @Romaine Lettuce{1}, leaving bottom of lettuce intact; quarter lengthwise into wedges. Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a large, dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @Bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat from pan. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop a few bacon slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings); set the rest aside.

Heat pan with reserved bacon fat over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4 servings) and @Sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4). Cook until caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash out pan.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce} and @Bold & Savory Steak Spice{1%tablespoon}; season with salt (we used ¾ tsp; use 1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) and pepper. Form into two patties (four for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun. Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add patties; cook ~{3-5%minutes} on first side. Flip, top with @Gouda Cheese{2%slice}, and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

While patties cook, in a second small bowl, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @Whole Grain Mustard{1%ounce}. In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} and half the @Ranch Spice{1%tablespoon} (use all for 4 servings); add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper. Halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2} until golden.

Fill toasted buns with patties, bacon slices, caramelized onion, and mayo-mustard sauce; divide between plates.

Serve with romaine wedges to the side; top with tomato, chopped bacon, and creamy herb dressing. Serve with potato wedges and remaining sauce for dipping.